API docs by Redocly

WebRobot ETL API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:

WebRobot Support: support@webrobot.eu License: Proprietary

API for managing projects, jobs, datasets, and ETL pipelines on WebRobot.

Authentication

The API uses API Keys for authentication. Include the X-API-Key header in all requests.

Base URL

  • Production: https://api.webrobot.eu/api
  • Development: http://localhost:8020/api

Rate Limiting

Requests are limited to 1000 requests per minute per API key.

EAN Plugin

Search and retrieve images for EAN products

Searches for images of products identified by EAN codes in the dataset of the specified country.

Returns images with:

  • Full image URL
  • Base64 data (if requested)
  • Similarity schours (0.0 - 1.0)
  • Additional metadata

Note:

  • Images are searched in the most recent available dataset
  • Results are sorted by descending score
  • The includeBase64 field in the request controls whether to include base64 data
Authorizations:
ApiKeyAuth
path Parameters
country
required
string
Example: denmark

ISO country code (e.g. "denmark", "italy", "france")

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Image search request for EAN products.

Specifies the EAN codes of products to search images for.

eans
required
Array of strings

List of EAN codes to search

includeBase64
boolean
Default: false

If true, includes base64 data of images

limit
integer
Default: 5

Maximum number of images per product

Responses

Production

https://api.webrobot.eu/api/webrobot/api/ean-image-sourcing/{country}/images

Local development

http://localhost:8020/api/webrobot/api/ean-image-sourcing/{country}/images

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
Example
{
  • "eans": [
    • "5901234123457"
    ]
}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 400
  • 404
Content type
application/json
{
  • "results": [
    • {
      • "ean": "5901234123457",
      • "images": [
        • {
          • "url": "https://example.com/image.jpg",
          • "base64": "string",
          • "schours": 0.85,
          • "source": "google_images"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
}

Get status of the last EAN job executed for a country

Returns information about the last EAN Image Sourcing job executed for the specified country.

Includes execution details such as:

  • Job status (PENDING, RUNNING, COMPLETED, FAILED)
  • Start and end timestamps
  • Execution time
  • Spark UI URL (if available)
  • Number of executor pods
  • Error messages (if failed)

ApiKeyAuth
path Parameters
country
required
string
Example: denmark

ISO country code (e.g. "denmark", "italy", "france")

Images

Search and retrieve images for EAN products

Searches for images of products identified by EAN codes in the dataset of the specified country.

Returns images with:

  • Full image URL
  • Base64 data (if requested)
  • Similarity schours (0.0 - 1.0)
  • Additional metadata

Note:

  • Images are searched in the most recent available dataset
  • Results are sorted by descending score
  • The includeBase64 field in the request controls whether to include base64 data

Execute a Spark job immediately

Executes a Spark job immediately, allocating resources in the Kubernetes cluster.

The job is executed with the configurations specified in the job itself or through optional parameters in the request.

Important notes:

  • The job must be associated with an agent with valid PySpark code
  • Cloud credentials are injected automatically if configured
  • The webhook is called automatically at start (RUNNING) and at the end (COMPLETED/FAILED)

Rate limiting: Max 10 concurrent executions per project

Mark zombie tasks as FAILED

Detects and marks as FAILED tasks that are RUNNING for longer than the specified timeout ("zombie" tasks).

A task is considered a "zombie" if:

  • It has status RUNNING
  • It has been running longer than the specified timeout (default: 24 hours)
  • The startedAt timestamp (or scheduledTime as a fallback) exceeds the timeout

When a task is marked as a zombie:

  • Status is updated to FAILED
  • executionLog is updated with FAILED status, completedAt, and an error message
  • Total execution duration is computed

Note: This endpoint requires admin privileges (scope admin).

Authorizations:
ApiKeyAuth
query Parameters
timeoutHours
integer <int64>
Default: 24
Example: timeoutHours=24

Timeout in hours to consider a task a "zombie" (default: 24). RUNNING tasks exceeding this value will be marked as FAILED.

Responses

Production

https://api.webrobot.eu/api/webrobot/api/projects/admin/tasks/mark-zombies

Local development

http://localhost:8020/api/webrobot/api/projects/admin/tasks/mark-zombies

  • 401
  • 500

  • "markedCount": 0,
  • "markedTaskIds": [
    • 0
    ],

Mark zombie tasks as FAILED

Detects and marks as FAILED tasks that are RUNNING for longer than the specified timeout ("zombie" tasks).

A task is considered a "zombie" if:

  • It has status RUNNING
  • It has been running longer than the specified timeout (default: 24 hours)
  • The startedAt timestamp (or scheduledTime as a fallback) exceeds the timeout

When a task is marked as a zombie:

  • Status is updated to FAILED
  • executionLog is updated with FAILED status, completedAt, and an error message
  • Total execution duration is computed

Note: This endpoint requires admin privileges (scope admin).

Authorizations:
ApiKeyAuth
query Parameters
timeoutHours
integer <int64>
Default: 24
Example: timeoutHours=24

Timeout in hours to consider a task a "zombie" (default: 24). RUNNING tasks exceeding this value will be marked as FAILED.

Responses

Production

https://api.webrobot.eu/api/webrobot/api/projects/admin/tasks/mark-zombies

Local development

http://localhost:8020/api/webrobot/api/projects/admin/tasks/mark-zombies

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "markedCount": 0,
  • "markedTaskIds": [
    • 0
    ],
  • "timeoutHours": 0,
  • "message": "Marked 5 zombie task(s) as FAILED"
}

Mark zombie tasks as FAILED

Detects and marks as FAILED tasks that are RUNNING for longer than the specified timeout ("zombie" tasks).

A task is considered a "zombie" if:

  • It has status RUNNING
  • It has been running longer than the specified timeout (default: 24 hours)
  • The startedAt timestamp (or scheduledTime as a fallback) exceeds the timeout

When a task is marked as a zombie:

  • Status is updated to FAILED
  • executionLog is updated with FAILED status, completedAt, and an error message
  • Total execution duration is computed

Note: This endpoint requires admin privileges (scope admin).

Authorizations:
ApiKeyAuth
query Parameters
timeoutHours
integer <int64>
Default: 24
Example: timeoutHours=24

Timeout in hours to consider a task a "zombie" (default: 24). RUNNING tasks exceeding this value will be marked as FAILED.

Responses

Production

https://api.webrobot.eu/api/webrobot/api/projects/admin/tasks/mark-zombies

Local development

http://localhost:8020/api/webrobot/api/projects/admin/tasks/mark-zombies

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "markedCount": 0,
  • "markedTaskIds": [
    • 0
    ],
  • "timeoutHours": 0,
  • "message": "Marked 5 zombie task(s) as FAILED"
}

ETL Execution

The job is executed with the configurations specified in the job itself or through optional parameters in the request.

Important notes:

  • The job must be associated with an agent with valid PySpark code
  • Cloud credentials are injected automatically if configured
  • The webhook is called automatically at start (RUNNING) and at the end (COMPLETED/FAILED)

Rate limiting: Max 10 concurrent executions per project

ApiKeyAuth

required

Example: 210

optional

If not provided, the job's default values are used.

List of cloud credential IDs to use

arguments
Array of strings

Additional arguments to pass to the Spark job
